{
  "stem": "17299.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 312.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then the worst part is, so for the camp administration, which were well nourished-- or camp police and things like that-- they sent them for RR to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there was an uproar in the ghetto over that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was an uproar in the ghetto when they come back, that the healthy ones were sent to the ghetto for rest and recreation and the sick ones were off to Salaspils.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the ghetto must have known what was going on in Salaspils, because there were not always 1,500 Jews there, on the ration.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Germans gave-- I don't think that the Germans gave over the rations for 1,500 Jews when they-- so many were dead every day.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they're pretty dumb in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was assigned in a hospital-- in Sala-- in a barrack hospital, even though I had no knowledge of it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And well, let's say above the naval, aspirin, below the naval, iodine.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had to go over the work kommando, on the second shift then, afterwards, choose either [INAUDIBLE] and a sawmill.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Somebody got injured to put a dressing on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Or somebody had temperature.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But if the temperature was under 102, don't give him any aspirin, because there is not enough aspirin around.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And some days I worked on a [NON-ENGLISH], on a sawmill and some days stayed in a hospital.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then the Latvian SS, what search us when we arrive-- and if they found somebody-- something on somebody what you feared-- you could trade for food, they were beating up.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They would hit him so much that he was bleeding all over.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Although I had a job, sometimes I have a dozen fellows to bandage, half the night, to stop the bleeding and everything.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
